## Step 4 — NEXT: Recommender

- `packages/api/src/recommendations/`:
  - `score.ts` — pure scoring function over a candidate `{ id, source: "event" | "live_event", taste }`.
  - `rules.ts` — typed editorial rules (`if cross_genre_bridge === "film" then boost ["film_score","cinematic"]`).
  - `diversity.ts` — top-N filter enforcing era/composer caps + ≥2 discovery items.
  - `pipeline.ts` — pulls candidates from both catalogs in parallel, scores, diversifies.
- tRPC: `recommendations.forUser({ limit, offset, surface })` — `surface` lets us reuse for home feed vs. profile vs. notification.
- Caching: Next.js `unstable_cache` keyed on `userId + lastDerivedAt`, TTL 6h. Invalidated by `revalidateTag("recs:" + userId)` from save/purchase mutations.
- **Method B (collaborative) skipped** until ≥100 active users (data model is ready for it).

---

## Step 5 — Visual cards onboarding

- New component `_components/taste-onboarding/visual-cards.tsx` — single-select / multi-select per spec section 3.4. One question per screen, swipe-feeling transitions.
- Resumes from `OnboardingSession.visualAnswers`.
- Mounted inside the existing `/onboarding` route; replaces the current Tanny-only flow as Phase 2 of the new state machine `idle → voice? → visual → clips → reveal → complete`.

---

## Step 6 — Clips phase

- Pull 10 clips from enriched `MUSIC_CATALOG` via a tiny picker that maximizes `(era × moodCluster)` coverage given partial profile.
- Auto-play, capture exact `listenedMs` on skip / `clip_complete` on natural end. Optional voice reaction stored as `voiceReaction`.
- Each interaction writes a `UserMusicEvent` (`clip_play`, `clip_skip`, `clip_complete`, `clip_replay`, `clip_voice_reaction`).
- On finish, mutation calls `tasteProfile.derive`, marks session `complete`.

---

## Step 7 — Reveal + `/profile/taste`

- Reveal: rotating loading messages → badge animates in → tags fade → summary → 2×2 cards.
- `/profile/taste`: read-only view + edit drawer that re-uses the visual card components. Edits call `tasteProfile.update`, invalidate recs cache.

---

## Step 8 — Event logger

- `apps/nextjs/src/lib/event-logger.ts`: client-side batcher (10s flush or 10 events). On `pagehide` flushes via `navigator.sendBeacon`.
- `apps/nextjs/src/app/api/events/route.ts`: REST POST shim — the **only** non-tRPC endpoint, because sendBeacon can't speak tRPC. Validates with `CreateUserMusicEventSchema`, requires Better Auth session.
- Wire from: event detail (`concert_view`), save toggle (`concert_save`), ticket success (`concert_purchase`), chat send (`search_query`).

---

## Step 9 (optional) — Voice phase integration

Wire the existing Tanny experience as Phase 1 of the new flow so users who prefer voice still get the rich derivation. The voice transcript already maps cleanly into the new `OnboardingSession.voiceTranscript`.

---

## Step 10 (optional) — Re-derivation cron

Weekly job that re-runs derivation for users with `lastDerivedAt < NOW() - 7d` AND ≥20 new `UserMusicEvent` rows since then. Same cron infrastructure as venue sync (Supabase pg_cron → Next.js API route).

